                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 12344/1.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Gregory</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-05-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 1, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 9, Honduranean series.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In reply to your serial No. 9 of March 20, 1908,
                    Honduranean series, relating to whether the Honduranean Government would be
                    willing, as an act of comity, to surrender fugitives from the justice of the
                    United States, charged with embezzlement, pending negotiations between the
                    Governments of the United States and Honduras for an extradition treaty, I have
                    the honor to inform you that the Honduranean Government will grant extradition
                    of fugitives if the crime is of recent date and the party or parties not
                    Honduraneans.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. H. Gregory</hi>, Jr.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
